This paper discusses the design of privacy policies with a focus on usability, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). However, the paper also deals with compliance with GDPR regulations, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR) and cyber law (cs.CY). The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques to improve privacy policies, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
